The theatre scene in Kenya is experiencing a great boost. Many theatre groups and companies in the capital city are producing theatre that is out of the box, contemporary and extremely relatable to the audiences. One such company is Aperture Africa Productions. With a long history of farces and comedy, the last weekend of February was no different. They brought their expertise back on the stage at the Oshwal Centre Auditorium, from February 24 to 26. The play was titled, &ldquo;It Runs In The Family&rdquo;, written by famous British playwright Ray Cooney. This version was ably directed by Amar Desai and starred Pritul Raithatha, Hiren Vara, Shelia Okatch, Nilofer Abji and Vikash Pattni, among others in prominent parts.The production was highly successful and drew a sufficient audience.